# file_contexts — maps filesystem paths to SELinux file labels.
#
# Format:  <path_regex>    <selinux_label>
#
# This entry labels /vendor/bin/safemoded with "safemoded_exec".
# When init exec's this file, SELinux sees:
#   - The file label: u:object_r:safemoded_exec:s0
#   - The init domain: u:r:init:s0
# The init_daemon_domain(safemoded) macro in safemoded.te defines the
# transition: init + safemoded_exec → safemoded domain.
# So the process runs as u:r:safemoded:s0.
#
# Without this entry, /vendor/bin/safemoded would get the default vendor
# label (u:object_r:vendor_file:s0) and NO domain transition would happen.
# init would log an error and refuse to start the service.
#
/vendor/bin/safemoded    u:object_r:safemoded_exec:s0
